class_data <- data %>%
  mutate(mode = ifelse(mode == "Major", 1, 0)) %>%
  select_if(is.numeric)
head(class_data)
## # A tibble: 6  13
##    mode danceability energy speechiness acousticness instrumentalness liveness
##   <dbl>        <dbl>  <dbl>       <dbl>        <dbl>            <dbl>    <dbl>
## 1     1        0.748  0.627      0.0639      0.131                  0   0.0852
## 2     0        0.353  0.755      0.733       0.0822                 0   0.39  
## 3     1        0.352  0.911      0.0747      0.00121                0   0.0995
## 4     1        0.62   0.625      0.553       0.287                  0   0.314 
## 5     1        0.687  0.781      0.053       0.0361                 0   0.0755
## 6     0        0.836  0.799      0.0873      0.187                  0   0.092 
## #  6 more variables: valence <dbl>, loudness <dbl>, tempo <dbl>,
## #   duration_ms <dbl>, weeks_on_chart <dbl>, streams <dbl>
heatmap(cor(class_data),
        col = colorRampPalette(c("darkgreen", "white", "red"))(100),
        symm = TRUE)

### Hypothesis 1
# *Songs classified as major mode are more likely to have higher danceability and valence scores compared to songs classified as minor mode.*

ad.test(class_data$danceability+class_data$valence)$p.value
## [1] 3.7e-24
hist(class_data$danceability+class_data$valence, col = "green")

sample <- sample(c(TRUE, FALSE), nrow(class_data), replace = TRUE, prob = c(0.7, 0.3))
train_data <- class_data[sample, ]
test_data <- class_data[!sample, ]

model_glm <- glm(mode ~ danceability + valence, data = train_data, family = binomial)
summary(model_glm)
## 
## Call:
## glm(formula = mode ~ danceability + valence, family = binomial, 
##     data = train_data)
## 
## Coefficients:
##              Estimate Std. Error z value Pr(>|z|)    
## (Intercept)   1.33489    0.15141   8.816  < 2e-16 ***
## danceability -1.44137    0.22927  -6.287 3.24e-10 ***
## valence      -0.05133    0.14054  -0.365    0.715    
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## (Dispersion parameter for binomial family taken to be 1)
## 
##     Null deviance: 6323.7  on 4648  degrees of freedom
## Residual deviance: 6275.9  on 4646  degrees of freedom
## AIC: 6281.9
## 
## Number of Fisher Scoring iterations: 4
plot(model_glm, which = 1)

coef(model_glm)
##  (Intercept) danceability      valence 
##   1.33488932  -1.44136602  -0.05133392
plot(class_data$danceability + class_data$valence, class_data$mode, xlab = "Danceability + valence", ylab = "Mode", pch = 19, col = ifelse(class_data$mode == 1, "green", "red"))
abline(model_glm, col = "black", lwd = 2)
## Warning in abline(model_glm, col = "black", lwd = 2): only using the first two
## of 3 regression coefficients
legend("topright", legend = c("Major Mode", "Minor Mode", "Logistic Regression Line"), col = c("green", "red", "black"), pch = c(1, 1, NA), lwd = c(NA, NA, 2))

roc <- rocit(class = model_glm$y, score = model_glm$fitted.values)
par(mfrow = c(1, 2))
plot(roc)
ksplot(roc)

par(mfrow = c(1, 1))
summary(roc)
##                             
##  Method used: empirical     
##  Number of positive(s): 2699
##  Number of negative(s): 1950
##  Area under curve: 0.5628
predicted_classes <- predict(model_glm, newdata = test_data, type = "response")
predicted_classes <- ifelse(predicted_classes > roc$AUC, 1, 0)

roc_curve <- roc(test_data$mode, predicted_classes)
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
plot(roc_curve, col = "green", main = "ROC Curve")

confusion_matrix <- caret::confusionMatrix(as_factor(predicted_classes), as_factor(test_data$mode), positive = "1")
ct <- confusion_matrix$table

TP <- ct[2, 2] # true positive
FP <- ct[2, 1] # false positive
TN <- ct[1, 1] # true negative
FN <- ct[1, 2] # false negative
P <- TP + FN # all positives (1)
N <- FP + TN # all negatives (0)

# confusion matrix heatmap
ggplot(as.data.frame(ct), aes(x = Reference, y = Prediction, fill = Freq)) +
  geom_tile(color = "white") +
  geom_text(aes(label = Freq), vjust = 1) +
  scale_fill_gradient(low = "white", high = "green") +
  labs(x = "Actual", y = "Predicted", title = "Confusion Matrix Heatmap")

print(paste("Accuracy: ", (TP + TN) / (P + N)))
## [1] "Accuracy:  0.54881974248927"
print(paste("Proportion of major mode (1): ", P / (P + N)))
## [1] "Proportion of major mode (1):  0.562231759656652"
print(paste("Proportion of minor mode (0): ", N / (P + N)))
## [1] "Proportion of minor mode (0):  0.437768240343348"
precision <- TP / (FP + TP)
print(paste("Precision: ", precision))
## [1] "Precision:  0.596279069767442"
recall <- TP / P
print(paste("Recall: ", recall))
## [1] "Recall:  0.611641221374046"
f1_score <- 2 * (precision * recall) / (precision + recall)
print(paste("F1 score: ", f1_score))
## [1] "F1 score:  0.603862458784739"
print(paste("Specificity: ", TN / (TN + FP)))
## [1] "Specificity:  0.468137254901961"

# Songs in the minor mode tend to have lower liveness scores.*
